CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper August 20, 1955, pg. 30. reads: "Friendly Benefactor - First teacher of Catherine Wallace was Miss Margaret Huey of the Fillion Studios. Mrs. Huey was not only Catherine's teacher, but her friend as well. There were many times Catherine didn't have the fee for a lesson, but that made no difference to Miss Huey. She had discovered a God-given gift and she wanted to work with it. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Margaret Huey at piano with singer Catherine Wallace beside her, looking at music in domestic interior
